description:
Naruto inches ever closer to discovering the true identity of his nemesis, Pain. But is it worth it as the frustrated ninja begins to morph at last into the dreaded Nine Tails? Plus an unexpected confession reveals incredible secrets about his past as Naruto prepares for the ultimate battle with Pain. Can the chakra-challenged Naruto win when one misstep could spell disaster?

  • Number 433: Sage Jutsu, a Mistake...?!
  • Number 434: Naruto vs. Tendo!!
  • Number 435: Banshoten'in! Universal Pull!!
  • Number 436: Peace
  • Number 437: Confessions
  • Number 438: The Seal Destroyed!!
  • Number 439: Catastrophic Planetary Construction
  • Number 440: The Conversation With Lord Fourth!!

description:
With the Dead Moon crisis past, Sailor Chibi Moon heading home to the 31st Century, and all the Sailor Soldiers reunited, everyone is content to begin living their lives normally again.

However, a new, and possibly the greatest, threat emerges. Sailor Galaxia, the Soldier of Destruction, wants the Silver Moon Crystal and the Sailor Crystals of the Solar System, and dispatches her Sailor Animamates to collect them.

Sailor Moon and the others are shocked that their enemies appear to be fellow Sailor Soldiers. Sailor Iron Mouse, Sailor Aluminum Siren, and Sailor Lead Crow, all loyal soldiers of Galaxia, arrive on Earth looking for the Sailor Crystals. But three new, mysterious allies appear, the Sailor Starlights. Sailor Star Fighter, Maker, and Healer, but whose side are they really on? Plus the arrival of a mysterious little girl who might or might not be Sailor Moon's second daughter from the future, and three pop stars becoming students at Usagi's high school.

As her friends and lover die before her eyes, will the future Sailor Moon knows ever come to pass? And if it does, will it be the same?
name: Vol. 1

description:
All of her friends have now been killed because of Sailor Galaxia. Her cat companions have been badly injured. And it seems the future will not arrive as it once was believed to.

Sailor Moon, now aided solely by the Sailor Starlights, their returned princess, and the mysterious little girl Chibi Chibi, must take the fight to Sailor Galaxia, the Soldier of Destruction, at her base at the end of the universe.

Meanwhile, who IS Galaxia? What are her motives? What is at Sagittarius Zero Star? And who, or what, is Chaos?
name: Vol. 2

description: MESSIAH WAR AFTERMATH! When X-Force was pulled into the future, what was forgotten in the present? The Leper Queen's murderous acts? The Sapien League's attack on the United Nations using two of the X-Men's students? Wolfbane's reunion with the Asgardian Wolf Prince? H.A.M.M.E.R.' s hunt for X-23? The wait is over. Find out who lives and who dies. Collecting X-FORCE #12-13, & 17-20.
name: Volume 3

description:
Along the Amazon river, the ship Boneca on which Mister No is traveling is attacked by a gang of pirates. Jerry kills one of the outlaws and discovers that he has a small silver jewel with him, shaped like a caiman. He decides to carry out his own inquiry, but the Manaus police boycott him. When he has all but given up on the investigation, Jerry receives some unanticipated help.

"Tutto Mister No" n. 8 released on January, 1990.
name: Il Caimano d'Argento

description:
Mister No has to fight against several fronts: he fights against the river pirates and the police, who put spokes in his wheels in every possible way. But he manages to discover the secret hideout of the criminals and even the disturbing identity of their captain

"Tutto Mister No" n. 9 released on February, 1990.
name: L'Uomo dalla Maschera Rossa

description:
One man against a gang of outlaws hiding in unhealthy marshes. A man alone against wild men and nature. But this man is called Mister No and he has overcome worse adversities. Whats more, one of the gang decides to help him and even the police join in to back him up. But it will not be a happy ending like in movies, no joyful cry here come our men to the rescue

"Tutto Mister No" n. 10 released on March, 1990.
name: I Pirati del Fiume

description:
Mister No is in Quito, the capital of Ecuador and, as usual, he is in the red: his last client paid him with false dollars It is no better with the next client, the photographer Brian Loger, who is actually a killer with the mission of murdering Tango Martnez, a ring-leader of the Mexican underworld, who is in Ecuador. The matter becomes even more complicated, when the other ring-leader joins the contest, Johnny Ricardo!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 11 released on April, 1990.
name: Avventura in Ecuador

description:
The gangland boss Johnny Ricardo wants Brian Loger to kill Tango Martnez, a guest in his wonderful villa. Mister No wants no part in it and risks his life to save a wily Mexican criminal, a braggart, but likeable in his own way like Tango. Yet again, Jerry Drake is alone against everyone!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 12 released on May, 1990.
name: "Tango" Martinez

description:
Dana Winter is a likeable Afro-American jazz pianist. Unluckily, he has a female name, and the clients of the night-club Alvorada, where he performs, expected a provocative full-busted singer Mister No saves Dana from the fury of the disappointed assailants and then he meets Patricia Rowland, an attractive archaeologist in search of Mayan Ruins in the Amazonian jungle

"Tutto Mister No" n. 13 released on June, 1990.
name: Rio Negro

description:
Mister No is the guide on Professor Warren and Patricias archaeological expedition, together with a friend Esse-Esse and the pianist Dana Winter. But they are hindered by the hostile nature of the jungle and some mysterious saboteurs.. They eventually manage to find a Maya Pyramid in the forest, but their troubles are not over

"Tutto Mister No" n. 14 released on July, 1990.
name: Ombre nella Notte

description:
The Tukano Indios, guided by the wise Fusiwe, do not want our men to enter the Mayan Pyramid: it is a sacred place, for them. And they are not wrong about its powers: the small temple is full of mortal traps that will strike the mysterious saboteurs of the expedition. But the most insidious danger for Mister No is the beautiful Patricia who, madly in love with him, is becoming a bit too possessive.

"Tutto Mister No" n. 15 released on August, 1990.
name: Il Tempio dei Maya

description:
The American Francis Stone claims to be a scholar and hires Mister No to transport pharmaceutical products with his plane. In actual fact, it is a question of a new type of narcotic, which Stone cultivates in his plantation. Jerry discovers his plan and has to fight alone against the narcotics trafficker and his men!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 16 released on September, 1990.
name: Uno Sporco Affare

description:
Hassler, an ex Nazi colonel, hires Mister No and Esse-Esse (who was his commander during the Second World War) for an expedition with the objective of studying the caimans of the upper Rio Demin. Mister No is approached by an American secret service agent, who hints at a mission, without however being able to explain what kind. For someone kills him.

"Tutto Mister No" n. 17 released on October, 1990.
name: Agente Segreto Zeta 3

description:
The expedition on the Rio Demin begins under a bad omen. The word has got around that the Amahinis, a kind of forest and water spirits, have appeared on the river. This time, the superstitious Brazilians are not wrong: Mister No and Esse-Esse are attacked by strange men with eyes that are similar to those of the caimans

"Tutto Mister No" n. 18 released on November, 1990.
name: Tragica Palude

description:
Colonel Hassle unveils his plans: he wants to reconstruct the German Reich in Amazonia, making use of genetically modified soldiers, in whose organism the respiratory apparatus of the caimans has been implanted! The amphibian soldiers seem invincible, and Mister No and Esse-Esse seem done for!. But the mutation of the caiman-men has a monstrous side effect.

"Tutto Mister No" n. 19 released on December, 1990.
name: "Operazione Poseidon"
Ne Sa Una Pi del Diavolo
